hopobject.body: Free medical insurance healthstate.lt That’s a point Emeritus spokeswoman Karen Lucas made in an April email for a Seattle Times story: “The national tragedy for millions of Americans is that the quality of life for both the caregiver and the cared-for is thoroughly compromised and the outcomes are sometimes horrible and deadly,” she wrote about home care for dementia patients. “Many seniors would live a far better quality of life in an assisted living community that’s staffed with 24/7 caregivers who are trained to provide the appropriate care.”
